{"questionId":"22646516","questionHtml":"<p>Given that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> has two <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>, find the probability that both <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> are greater than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Z</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)</strong></em> for obtaining <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math> from solving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> and award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for stating the correct inequality.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)(A1)</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)(A0)</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>Z</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for rearranging to form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>Z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> and then attempting to square both sides <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>Z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>Z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempts to calculate their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>both</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>053005</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to calculate their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>both</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>|</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>‐</mo><mi>intercepts</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>053005</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>317310</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>167</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22646516","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.2h","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that the graph of f has two x-intercepts, X1 and X2, find the probability that both X1 and X2 are greater than 0.5.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}